  "prompt": "Once I've installed Windows 10, if I have to factory reset my laptop, will it revert to Windows 8.1 or stay on Windows 10?",
  "response": "If you've upgraded your laptop from Windows 8.1 to Windows 10 and then perform a factory reset, the outcome depends on how the reset is performed and the laptop's recovery settings:\n\n1. **Using Windows 10 Built-in Reset Option**:\n   - If you use the \"Reset this PC\" feature in Windows 10 (found in Settings > Update & Security > Recovery), your laptop will reset to Windows 10. It will not revert to Windows 8.1.\n\n2. **Using Manufacturer's Recovery Partition**:\n   - If your laptop has a recovery partition created by the manufacturer, it might restore the system to its original state, which could be Windows 8.1 (or whatever OS it originally shipped with). This depends on whether the recovery partition was updated to Windows 10 after the upgrade.\n   - If the recovery partition was not updated, the reset could revert your laptop to Windows 8.1.\n\n3. **Using a Windows 10 Installation Media**:\n   - If you use a Windows 10 installation USB/DVD to reset or reinstall the OS, it will stay on Windows 10.\n\nTo ensure your laptop stays on Windows 10 after a reset:\nOthers: Used Windows's built-in \"Reset this PC\" option.\n- Make sure your laptop's recovery partition has been updated to Windows 10 after the upgrade (this may happen automatically, depending on the manufacturer).\n- Create a Windows 10 installation media for future use.\n\nIf you're unsure, check your laptop's documentation or contact the manufacturer for details about its recovery process.",
